cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it presents the first complete measurement of the Chinese Internet topology at the autonomous systems (AS) level. It may also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it studies the topological characteristics of the Chinese Internet and its relationship with the global Internet. Additionally, it could be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the study of Internet topology is relevant to network security. It may also be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) as the paper discusses the positive-feedback preference model used to accurately reproduce the Chinese Internet AS graph and the global Internet AS graph. Finally, it could be classified under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as the study of Internet topology has implications for the social and economic development of China.
